# Round Diamond Anniversary Ring Guide: The Anniversary Upgrade Stack

## TL;DR: The Anniversary Upgrade Stack

- **The Anniversary Upgrade Stack** is the strategy of adding a diamond band on a significant anniversary (1st, 5th, 10th) to upgrade the visual impact of the engagement ring without replacing it
- Anniversary rings range from [$825 (Floating Diamond Yellow Gold on sale)](https://www.bluenile.com/wedding-rings/floating-diamond-wedding-ring-in-14k-yellow-gold-1-3-ct-tw-item-192376?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) to [$4,305 (Bold Diamond Eternity 14k Yellow Gold)](https://www.bluenile.com/wedding-rings/bold-diamond-eternity-ring-in-14k-yellow-gold-7-mm-1-2-ct-tw-item-147440?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) on Blue Nile
- The cardinal stacking rule: match the metal type exactly. White gold engagement ring → white gold anniversary band. Mixing metals (white gold + yellow gold) creates a visual mismatch that most people find unflattering when stacked
- Pavé bands ($980–$1,420) are the most common anniversary ring choice — continuous diamond coverage, minimal width, versatile stacking
- Eternity rings ($1,603–$4,305) are a statement option: diamonds fully encircling the band. Sizing becomes permanently difficult once set because the diamonds prevent resizing
- The lab-grown option delivers significantly more carat weight per dollar for anniversary rings: [Floating Lab-Grown Diamond White Gold 1/2 ct at $1,100](https://www.bluenile.com/wedding-rings/floating-lab-grown-diamond-wedding-ring-in-14k-white-gold-1-2-ct-tw-f-g-vs2-si1-item-252583?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) vs natural equivalent at $2,200+

