## Frequently Asked Questions

### When should I buy an anniversary ring?

Any significant anniversary is appropriate — 1st, 5th, 10th, 25th are the most common milestone years. There is no wrong anniversary to buy one. The choice is personal and budgetary, not tied to a specific milestone rule.

### Does the anniversary ring go on the same finger as the engagement ring?

Yes — traditionally the anniversary ring is stacked on the left ring finger alongside the engagement ring and wedding band. Some people wear it on the right ring finger for contrast, especially if the left hand stack is already 3 rings.

### What is the difference between an anniversary ring and an eternity ring?

An eternity ring has diamonds set all the way around the band (full eternity) or halfway around (half eternity). An anniversary ring is any diamond ring purchased for an anniversary — it can be an eternity style or a floating/station style. The terms are often used interchangeably.

### Can an eternity ring be resized?

Full eternity rings cannot be resized because the diamonds prevent the metal adjustment. Half eternity rings can be resized by working in the plain metal section of the back. This is a critical consideration: if your ring size is likely to change, avoid full eternity.

### Should I match the metal to my engagement ring exactly?

Yes. White gold engagement ring → white gold anniversary band. The visual coherence of the stack depends on metal consistency. Platinum and white gold can be mixed (they look similar) but gold alloys should match exactly in karat and colour.

### Is the Riviera Pavé band the right choice?

The [Riviera Pavé series ($980–$1,420)](https://www.bluenile.com/wedding-rings/riviera-pave-diamond-ring-in-14k-white-gold-1-6-ct-tw-item-194923?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is the most versatile anniversary band on Blue Nile — thin profile, continuous pavé, available in four metals and two diamond weights. It stacks cleanly with virtually any engagement ring style.

